
[1]crumble

   CRUMBLE, v.t. [G.] To break into small pieces; to divide into minute
   parts.

   CRUMBLE, v.i.

   1. To fall into small pieces; to break or part into small fragments.

   I a stone is brittle, it will crumble into gravel.

   2. To fall into decay; to perish; as, our flesh shall crumble into
   dust.
